@startuml
title EduSecure - Lecturer Submission Retrieval and Server-Side Decryption

actor "Assignment-owning Lecturer" as Lecturer
participant "SubmissionController" as Controller
participant "SubmissionService" as Service
participant "AssignmentService" as AssignmentService
database "SubmissionRepository\n(PostgreSQL)" as SubmissionRepo
collections "FileSystemSubmissionContentStore\n(./var/submission-storage)" as FileStore
participant "SubmissionKeyProtectionService\n(AESWrap)" as KeyProtection
participant "SubmissionContentEncryptionService\n(AES-GCM)" as ContentCrypto
participant "AuditService" as Audit

Lecturer -> Controller : GET /api/submissions/{submissionId}/content
Controller -> Service : getSubmissionContent(submissionId, authentication)

Service -> Service : find current user by email
Service -> SubmissionRepo : findById(submissionId)
SubmissionRepo --> Service : submission metadata

Service -> AssignmentService : requireLecturerOrAdminAssignmentAccess(...)
AssignmentService --> Service : access granted for assignment owner

Service -> FileStore : read(storedFileReference)
FileStore --> Service : ciphertext bytes

Service -> KeyProtection : unwrap(wrappedContentEncryptionKey, storageKeyVersion)
activate KeyProtection
KeyProtection -> KeyProtection : load submission.storage.master-key
KeyProtection -> KeyProtection : restore per-submission AES key with AESWrap
KeyProtection --> Service : plaintext content-encryption key
deactivate KeyProtection

Service -> ContentCrypto : decrypt(ciphertext, storageEncryptionNonce, contentEncryptionKey)
activate ContentCrypto
ContentCrypto -> ContentCrypto : AES/GCM/NoPadding decrypt
ContentCrypto --> Service : plaintext submission bytes
deactivate ContentCrypto

Service -> Audit : record(SUBMISSION_CONTENT_ACCESSED)
Audit --> Service : audit recorded

Service --> Controller : SubmissionContentResponse(fileName, contentType, plaintext bytes)
Controller --> Lecturer : 200 OK attachment download

note right of Lecturer
The lecturer does not decrypt locally.
They request content through the API.
end note

note right of Service
Server-side decryption only happens after:
- submission lookup
- lecturer ownership/admin access check
- wrapped key restoration
- AES-GCM decryption
end note

note over FileStore,SubmissionRepo
At rest, the file remains split across:
- ciphertext in the file store
- nonce + wrapped key + key version in metadata
end note

@enduml


